r and sacred forms and accounts of travel. Above all, the papers reveal the self-generating and multiple-authored characteristics of pilgrimage narrative: stories of past pilgrimage experience generate future stories and even future journeys.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aChristian pilgrims and pilgrimages in literature. 0aChristian pilgrims and pilgrimagesxHistory. 0aTravel in literature. 0aTravel writingxHistory. 7aTravel / Special Interest / Religious.2bisacsh1 aColeman, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColeman, Simon, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aElsner, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElsner, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLock, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManiura, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMitchell, Hildi J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetsalis-Diomidis, Alexia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Wes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178533061240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781785330612423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781785330612/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK